      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping between simulation input parameters and experimental control variables demonstrated; dimensional analysis confirms equivalency.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the simulation inputs are straightforwardly derived from the bench test control variables and that no formal equivalency analysis is warranted, as the correspondence is considered self-evident given the direct use of measured values as boundary conditions. A structured equivalency assessment was therefore not conducted. This factor is treated as not applicable in practice; however it is recorded here as not-assessed rather than not-applicable pending a formal scoping decision by the responsible engineer."
